I look at it this way.  This is about the U.S. to me, not about Israel.  From my objective, neutral perspective, Israel, given all of the massive problems that come with it, is more of a burden to the U.S., than an asset.  The U.S. has allies all along the borders of the Middle East now, NATO encompasses almost all of Europe, we are on good terms with Pakistan now, not to mention several Arab countries as well, so people still want to feed the bullshit that Israel is a "strategic" ally?  My idea of strategic is to say to Israel "you are going to swallow the international solution son, because I am tired of shouldering the load for you."  When Israel cries "but everyone is anti-semitic!", our strategic response is "Tough shit son.  I would prefer a solution that might be a little unfair toward you than having to stand next to you and get bitch slapped by the world for another 100 years, because you are paranoid about everyone's motivations."<P>Frankly, given the position Israel is in right now, with so many enemies, how is it realistic to expect to have your cake and eat it too?  Sure, the international solution will not be entirely in favor Israel.  It will be neutral.  How will it be guaranteed to be neutral?  Hmm, perhaps because Israel's big brother the U.S. will be sitting in that international tribunal carrying around a very big hammer to ensure Israel isn't forced to bend over too much.  What is more, regardless of how anti-semitic the solution is, the end result will be the world acting as Israel's bodyguard, waiting at the ready to "Afghanistan" any Arab country that continues promoting violence against Israel.  Where would be the anti-semitism in that?<P>Now comes the funny part.  Here I am talking about how I view Israel neutrally.  I view Israel from the standpoint of an American who wants what is best for America, period.  But given the way things are in this country, if people dare discuss Israel in a neutral manner, based solely upon its utility to America, I am viewed as borderline anti-semitic for having these views.  As if unless I am 100% behind Israel, I am anti-semitic.  Uh, fuck you.  I am neutral here in the sense that all I want is what is best for the USA - the greatest country in the history of the world.  Far greater and endlessly more important to me personally than Israel.  <P>Getting to the simple point here, Israeli and American paranoia that the world is anti-semitic to me is not justification enough to forego an international solution to the Middle Eastern crisis.  It is just a weak and sorry excuse by whiny babies who want to have cake while lunatics all over the place are scrambling to find weapons to kill them with.<p>[ April 30, 2002: Message edited by: Lizard ]<P>--------------------<P>Scaled, for her pleasure<BR><A HREF="http://drow.org/eq/roster/viewprofile.php?name=Sssorn" TARGET=_blank>Profile</A> | <A HREF="http://www.drow.org/news.shtml" TARGET=_blank>BotS</A>
