I dunno about anyone else, but someone is not my enemy unless they actually say so.  There are plenty of people that dislike who I am, the things I do, and who I associate with, but I don't consider them my enemies.<P>I wouldn't say that the Arabs are our enemies.  I would say that they may really dislike, or even hate us.  Who am I, though, to question what motives they have, or to presume they are going to act upon those motives.  It would be wise to take caution, but attacking them merely because they "hate" us is illogical and immoral.<P>I tend to agree with Sssorn, Israel pretty much is the reason that several Arab nations dislike us.  I don't think they are a buffer, but rather the cause.<P>As for the solution:  The international isn't on the same page as us.  I do not think that they are going have the bravado that it takes to fix this "problem" up.  There are other, non-war-related reasons that several European nations are refusing to support the US.  The entire issue delves into the world of socio-economic imperialism that is inherent in the capital system of the United States.<P>--------------------<P>El Jobo Cleric
