Marlonius you have my complete respect and admiration as a member of our military.  Defending the United States of America and all of the wonderful things this country stands for is nobility exemplified.  Cheers to you mate. <P>I appreciate the posts.  I realize none of us are experts in the field here, but one thing I have learned in my 33 years is that there is always something to be learned from the wisdom of common folk.<P>It is disheartening that the only legitimate caveat to the "international solution" concept I laid out is a deep distrust for the international community and fears of international anti-semitism.  I personally have a little more faith in the international community than that, having lived in five different countries for extended periods myself.  How can Israel ever really hope to be embraced by the world if it never reaches out and says "I have faith and trust you"?  Where will this ever really get Israel or the U.S. down the road other than to further alienation, distrust and hatred?<P>I think it is time to reach out to the world and say we are all brothers here and we have a problem.  Let's come together and solve it by showing good faith and trust in each other.  The breach between Israel and the Arabs is too deep and too painful to heal, but the breach between Israel/USA and the rest of the world is not.  That is where the solution should lie if you ask me.<p>[ April 30, 2002: Message edited by: Lizard ]<P>--------------------<P>Scaled, for her pleasure<BR><A HREF="http://drow.org/eq/roster/viewprofile.php?name=Sssorn" TARGET=_blank>Profile</A> | <A HREF="http://www.drow.org/news.shtml" TARGET=_blank>BotS</A>
