Howdy all,<P>Interesting discussion here.  I think for the most part it has been completely off on a tangent it is still interesting.  I won't be posting any nonsense about who is right or wrong myself as I am in full agreeance with you Sssorn that at this point it is irrelevant.  <P>I just wanted to pose a question to your solution.  I like your solution for the most part but I get hung up on one part.  The disciplinary action as a result of one side breaking the rules.  So far we have only heard that it would most likely be the Arabs who would break the rules and then we could proceed to wipe them out.  That could very well happen if this solution were to be the route taken by the international community.  <P>My question is, what would happen if Isrealis broke the rules? How fast would we see the world taken action on them?  Would US and the international community come down hard and swiftly on them?  How would big corporations that have financial stake in that region of the world influence this?<P>I think the only way it could work is if the international community could assure both sides that they would be completely unbiased.  Make no mistake, in this situation if Israel broke the rules first we had better be prepared to send them packing just as fast as we would do to the Palestinians.  Other than that it seems about the best plan I've heard yet.<P>Fobban
