I like to see people place restrictions on an Israeli response. It really is cute. There is a real old philosophy that says to prevent someone from committing a violation of your natural rights you have the right to do ANYTHING that prevents that from happening. It's really the only sort of idea that guarantees your rights are not violated. There has never been any event in history where group A has killed group B, and by group B giving group A something has group B gained a long lasting peace. In this situation its more than obvious. If you create a government around a terrorist leadership, you create a terrorist state. A terrorist state on the boarder of a state which is by far the most currently threatened country in the world.<P>You ponder the question, what if Israel broke some rules first. I highly doubt this would ever happen unless out of defense of their natural rights. I give them credit where it is due, they could easily have done much more than they did, but we stepped in and told them not to. <P>I like the tangents we slide off to about investment in Israel. It all boils down to the same impotent idea. That economically prosperous people always mistreat people who are not economically prosperous. That for some reason simply because Israel has more money than the people in the palestinian occupied territories that they for some reason are the reason that the palestinians are destitute, poor, ill fed, etc.<P>To understand that you have to move to a discussion of Africa, a series of countries where most people are poor and there are even greater civil wars. The only difference is we have no investment in the area and so therefore do about nothing to solve the problems of that area. The people there are not poor directly as a result of some rich country misusing some poor country, it is because warlords steal from the people, misuse their trust, steal aid sent to the area and use it to fund their civil wars. You know what I think, and maybe I am just out there, but I think that the reason the palestinians are poor and destitute is not because the Israeli's go out of their way to cause it, but because maybe a dictator is chosing to misuse and abuse his people in an effort to promote a goal which is much similar to the africa goal which is an attempt to kill a group of people whom they do not simply like.<P>I know you hate how I don't throw out some political solution here for you all to be amazed at. But I like studying history and in history, no problem like this has ever been solved by appeasing murderers. Some day a palestinian state may be there and maybe it should, but you can't do it under these circumstances.<P>--andrew
