Wow! Too bad I never visited the DROW forums before this. Definetely some interesting and intelligent (for the most part) discussions going on here. <P>As for my opinion on the middle east situation:<P>(After I finished writing this I realized it is very long, but action packed, so try at least to read it all.)<P>Israel has been justified in everything they have done since 1948. They have done everything correctly since 1948 EXCEPT for allowing international pressure to hinder their self defense measures. If you sat at a desk, for 54 years, and on some days had one kid throwing a ball at your head, on other days several kids doing it, would you not just take the ball away? Or even more, throw the ball back... real hard? Sure you would. If the teacher in the class let the ball throwing at your head slide by, and then criticized you strongly every time you took the ball away would you give a damn? You bet not, you'd do whatever you could in your self defense. Furthermore, if the teacher did this, would you not suspect the teacher had a hidden agenda... or at least something against you? I know I would. Granted now, this is an oversimplification of a very complex issue, but the analogy holds. <P>For 54 years, Israel, the only home of the Jews has been struggling with ball throwers, and prejudice teachers. Would you stand by and let your daughter or son, or mother, or father, get blown up? Would you not flinch if the Smiths who lived next door for 10 years were one day all wiped off the face of the earth? Or maybe the Johnson family was at a Johnson family reunion, and the hall they rented out was blasted to bits. Good-bye Johnsons! I don't think anyone could say they would stand by.<P>Although it has become cliche these days to say oh.. occupation, yes BUT... occupation, occupation, occupation, occupation! God damnit, Im tired as hell hearing about occupation. First of all, I could present you with a list of over 50 MAJOR terrorist attacks PRE-1967 (yep got that list saved on my computer). Furthermore, as most of you are Americans, I will take the story home. Do you call, Florida, or California "Occupied territories"? Like hell you do! However, on some day in the distant history the U.S. annexed these terrirtories from the Spanish. That's right, they took it with bloodshed, for no real cause other than to expand their borders. You don't hear Mexicans demanding "right of return", they don't cry "Oh woe, my great great great great great etc. Grandfather's home was knocked over and burned by American troops, and I want the land back." <P>In 1967 the Arabs fucked up and attacked Israel after they had failed in all prior attempts. How bloody arogant they are to demand territory back that they lost when THEY attacked Israel. The worst part is that people actually support this shit. Not to mention the fact that in 1948 every one of the Arabs living in Israel was offered full citizenship. Would have been better off if you ask me. The right to vote, a good economy, democracy... <P>Someone said it before, Islamic fundamentalists (terrorists) would love to see all of the non-Muslims wiped off the face of the earth. I'm starting to get the sense that more and more, the feeling is mutual. Everyone knows many Arab children learn in school and through textbooks to hate Jews, what most don't know, is that it's not just Jews.. Mr. Christian, you're next, Smiling Buddhist? You're outta here. We already know the Arabs hate Hindus... Pakistan and Arabia Vs. India Round 2. <P>For a long time most Israelis (Jewish or not) and most Jews always thought only of the olive branch. Make peace they said, give them a chance, we will have peace in the land of Israel. Lately, that sentiment is diminishing. I personally have almost exhausted my naive faith that somehow peace will be achieved. How many chances do you give the man who, every summer, runs up to your home and stomps down your flowers? You tell him every year to stop, but every year he is back... with bigger boots... killing more flowers. The time for the Arabs is up.. and I say Arabs and not Palestinians, because for the most part they are in it together. Yes, I sound racist, I'm not going to deny it. You loose family members to suicide bombers, and then hear about all the people who cheer the bombers on, and who support the bombers with cash, and try and fucking not be a racist. I have ONE Muslim friend. Fortunately she agrees with me on the Mid-East issues, and that is why she lives in Canada. I don't hate all Arabs, I am sure there are plenty of peaceknick Arabs out there, just not enough. <P>Pretty much since Muhamad died, the Arab culture has disented into an anarchistic, hedonistic, and corrupt society. It is sad, but true. Dictators live in palaces with gold lined walls (watch CNN videos of GWB meetings with Arab leaders) while their oppressed people live in shacks with walls lined with mold. The worst part is, the Arabs dont revolt against it. They revolt against American capitalism, or Israeli freedom. <P>I read a few interesting articles about Islam today. Seems Israel and the U.S. aren't the only victims... far from it. They are the only two nations that have press on it. The U.S. because it is the U.S. and Israel because it gets so much of it. The fact though is, that nearly every country in the world has at one time or another been the victim of Islamic terrorism. Are they rebelling against France's support of Israel? I would balk at that considering France's Anti-Semitic track record. Perhaps the Philipenes are being targeted for the billions they send Israel each year? Oh wait they don't, do the two countries even have formal relations? Perhaps it is the fact that the Philipenes are occupied territories, or ancestral Islamic territory? No on two counts. The second article I read brought to light another interesting fact. "The biggest victims of Islamic terorism are Arabs." Yep, poor Israel can no longer claim it is the biggest victim, how dare they as a matter of fact! We all know that More Arabs die each year to the hands of Arab terrorists. <P>When I visited Israel 4 years ago, before the intifada, I remember the ultimate goal for the nation at the time was re-planting of forests. Israel is the only country trying to teraform the land into what it once was before Arab colonization decimated it's forests. That's right, the Galilee and most of Israel was a lush paradise. So was a lot of the middle east. I remember standing on the hills overlooking a forest who's name I can not remember. It stood out like a sore thumb, and patriotic Canadian that I am, few forests in Canada could compare in beauty. Terrorism was out of my mind momentarily, all the Arabs who wanted to kill me and my family forget them. I was lost in the moment, I was awe struck, and frankly, travelling through the Holy land that was not the only time. Be you Christian or Jew, I'll bet you any money that if you land in Israel, the moment you disembark the plane you will feel something. An unparalelled feeling of familiarity. I have been here before was what the video records me as saying. The smell, so different from anywhere I had ever been, the air so thick with je ne sais quoi. <P>Now when I try and conjur up those feelings again, all I feel is anger. Anger knowing that millions of evil-doers would seek to undo what the Israelis of today have wrought. Anger, that I can not visit my ancestral home for fear of my life. Angry that the British, and the French, and a whole bunch of Europeans are so blinded by their hate, that they can not see what really goes on. When God said that the Israelites were his chosen people, I doubt this was what he had in mind. To be targeted by hatred for decades without number. For what reason? I will let Sushi answer, he is clearly anti-semitic. I would not for a moment hesitate to call him that. The fact that he calls that site he posted another view, or factual in any way is enough to make my mouth bitter. If every piece of "news" was not about some atrocity Israel comitted I might believe it was an online paper with a lot of bias... Clearly the junk the people on that site conjur up is without a drop of truth in the bucket. If Israel really has such a large spy network all over... everywhere, and is so talented at creating anthrax and deploying it, perhaps they could deploy some of their anthrax to the owners/operators of that site. <P>If anyone read about, or was at or saw the pro-Israel vs. Pro-Arab (Again I say Arab, because they are all in it together. Furthermore no such thing as "palestine" exists)rallies in Washington, or Ottawa, clear distinct differences could be found. If you were a deaf man at the Pro-Israel rallies you would have seen Israeli flags flown high, signs condeming Arafat, signs condeming terrorists, signs of Christian support groups, signs calling for.... peace. If you were a deaf man at the Pro-Arab rallies you would have seen Palestinian flags flown high, with Israeli flags burning, or being stomped on on the ground, you would have seen signs equating Zionism with racism, slanderous attacks at Jews, Christians, the U.S. and Israel/Israelis plastered all over boards in the air.  If you were a blind man at the Pro-Israel Rallies you would have heard impassioned speaches about suffering, death by terrorism, the need to root out evil, and bring the good Arabs to power, Israeli songs of harmony and support for Israel, speeches about how loss of life on either side is a loss, speeches about peace... If you were a blind man at a pro-Arab raid... er rally you would have heard chants of Death to Israel, Down with American capitalism, speeches about Israel being a terrorist state, speeches about how America is a corrupt country with a terrorist government, speeches about war...<BR>Anyone who says otherwise is a liar, I was there, I saw it, I heard it I am neither blind nor-deaf. <P>You can drive from anywhere in Israel to any other place in Israel in one day. It would take you a whole lot longer to travel in a straight line from the southmost border of Arabia, to the Northmost, in a straight line no less. I'd wager (and don't quote me, because it is only a guess and is not backed up by fact, only observation) that if you took all of the 53 Arab nations and combined them into one, you would have a land mass, comparable, or larger than the U.S. with plenty of room for 2.5 million Arabs with "no place to go". There is your solution. If these other Arab nations really "care" so much for the "victims of Israeli oppression" perhaps they would be so malevolent as to take these poor suffering souls under their wing. There are a plenty of dictatorships in the middle-east with governments just as corrupt as the one Arafat tries to lead, why do we need another one just like it?<P>Edit: I forgot to thank Xwar for his post. Who knows it better than someone who experiences it first hand?<p>[ May 08, 2002: Message edited by: Alistriwen ]
</FONT>
